//
// test/sema/emit-ast-resolved/byte_stable.test — `sema-stability.contract.md`
// Invariant 1 (T036 of `specs/006-m3-sema/tasks.md`). Asserts that
// `nslc -emit=ast` produces byte-identical stdout across two
// invocations on the same input.
//
// Failure mode: any nondeterminism in the post-Sema printer (e.g.,
// iterating a `DenseMap` directly without sorting) would make the
// two runs diverge; `diff` then exits non-zero and the test fails.
//
// Failing-state evidence (FR-029): a hypothetical regression that
// drops Principle V's deterministic-pipeline guarantee fails this
// fixture as the first observable byte difference.
//
// RUN: printf 'module hello {\n  reg q[8] = 0;\n}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl > %t.run1.txt
// RUN: %nslc -emit=ast %t.nsl > %t.run2.txt
// RUN: diff %t.run1.txt %t.run2.txt
